about.project.description.message: RUYISDK is a full-featured, integrated development environment tailored for RISC-V developers. Led by the Institute of Software, Chinese Academy of Sciences (ISCAS), RUYISDK aims to provide a one-stop development solution for RISC-V developers. The project was planned in the second half of 2022 and adopted a biweekly agile release cadence starting in early 2024. Since its inception we continually refine the product to provide high-quality support to the RISC-V community.

about.goals.item1.message: Ensure that developers using (almost) any RISC-V board or module can obtain hardware documentation, firmware/software updates, and debugging support through RUYISDK.

about.goals.item2.message: Allow developers to specify common RISC-V ISA extension combinations and generate the required OS, toolchains, language runtimes/VMs, libraries, and application frameworks via the RUYISDK system.

about.goals.item3.message: Foster and operate an active, inclusive developer community.

我们的代码完全开源，意味着每个人都可以在许可证允许的条件下查看、使用、修改和共享.message: Our code is completely open source, which means everyone can view, use, modify and share it under the conditions permitted by the license. Whether you are a developer, student, enthusiast or enterprise, you can freely participate in our project and build a better RuyiSDK together. Welcome to join our community and promote the development of open source together!

节日快乐！PLCT实验室与玄铁RV学院联合推出「RISC-V学习+实践指南」，助.message: Happy holidays! The PLCT Lab and XuanTie RV Academy have jointly launched the "RISC-V Learning + Practice Guide" to help you improve your skills during the holidays. The XuanTie RISC-V Academy provides free series courses covering three levels: beginner, intermediate, and advanced. Taught by experienced experts, these courses cover various aspects of RISC-V, including software development, hardware acceleration, and system architecture. Now, we are also launching the "CIE-XuanTie Cup RISC-V Application Innovation Competition" with three major tracks: hardware acceleration, server components, and smart hardware. Challenge yourself to apply your knowledge and win prizes! Join the RISC-V learning feast and make the most of your holidays!

openGauss RISC-V SIG深度参与openGauss Meetup.message: openGauss RISC-V SIG Deeply Participates in the openGauss Meetup Chengdu Station, Exploring the Fusion and Practice of Open Source Databases and RISC-V

2025年9月27日，openGauss Meetup成都站成功举办。openG.message: On September 27, 2025, the openGauss Meetup Chengdu Station was successfully held. The core team of the openGauss RISC-V SIG made a dazzling appearance, sharing their important progress in the RISC-V architecture: implemented the openGauss container deployment solution and completed the migration from 5.1.0 to 7.0.0, with significant performance improvements. Currently, the community is actively promoting technical optimization and ecosystem building, and launching the [Jichen Plan] internship recruitment, inviting developers to join, and contributing to the development of the open source database in the RISC-V ecosystem. Join us to explore the future of RISC-V!

首届“合肥RISC-V开放日”在合肥工业大学顺利举行，生态成果喜人.message: The First "Hefei RISC-V Open Day" was held successfully at Hefei University of Technology, with a successful outcome.

2025年9月24日，首届[合肥RISC-V开放日]在合肥工业大学成功举行。活动.message: On September 24, 2025, the first [Hefei RISC-V Open Day] was held successfully at Hefei University of Technology. The event gathered over 100 experts and scholars to discuss the development of the RISC-V software and hardware ecosystem. Red Hat, PLCT Lab, and other institutions shared their innovative practices in operating systems, AI, and education, and set up an ecosystem exhibition to showcase the latest results of openKylin and deepin. This event established a crucial platform for industry-university-research cooperation and promoted the harmonious development of the RISC-V ecosystem.
